            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "PART 5 ORGANIZATION OF A CONSOLIDATION AND FAST CLOSE"
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.121,
                0.367,
                0.138
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Define some thresholds"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.155,
                0.868,
                0.204
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "In order to reduce the number of consolidation adjustments, get the Auditors' agreement on some thresholds whether for intercompany differences or events related to group transactions."
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.219,
                0.696,
                0.236
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Be sure to aet some assistance from expert consultant"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.251,
                0.868,
                0.348
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "For a group having an oversized consolidation team with a high level of expertise it makes no sense for one or two consolidations a year. It is much more efficient to manage a reasonable number of persons having a strong knowledge of all group companies and all events related to them. Of course these few people must also have a rather good knowledge of consolidation techniques."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.363,
                0.29,
                0.379
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "This is a minimum."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.395,
                0.868,
                0.46
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Now, these persons can leave the company, can be temporarily ill or just be faced to some difficult consolidation problems. The wise situation in order to avoid planning delay is to be able to count on the assistance of an external expert consultant, in such situations."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.476,
                0.508,
                0.492
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "This is also a way to secure the planning."
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.526,
                0.543,
                0.547
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "3.3 After the consolidation"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.569,
                0.868,
                0.602
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "When the consolidation process is achieved there are still so many things to complete."
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.617,
                0.608,
                0.634
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Maximize automatic production of disclosures"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.65,
                0.868,
                0.698
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "The most important task between the end of the 'technical' step of the consolidation and the Auditors conclusions is the production of the consolidated disclosures (notes to the accounts)."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.714,
                0.653,
                0.73
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "There are two issues if we want to optimize the process."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.746,
                0.868,
                0.826
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "First, as the disclosures consist mainly in figures in Excel spreadsheets and comments in Word documents, the final product is a merge of both. Today, some consolidation software offer solutions to link these spreadsheets directly to the consolidation data base and give the assurance that when opening these documents all figures are refreshed with the last version."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.827,
                0.868,
                0.859
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Moreover, it is also possible to imbed all these spreadsheets in a Word document."
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "header",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.07,
                0.371,
                0.085
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "DIRECT CONSOLIDATION"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.123,
                0.885,
                0.188
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Secondly, we are convinced that a large part of the comments on the accounts can be prepared before the consolidation is actually done. This means that part of this task should be prepared in December the latest before the closing."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.203,
                0.885,
                0.252
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "The experience pictured from some groups has shown that taking these two issues into account has reduced the disclosures task from two or three weeks to a couple of days."
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.267,
                0.547,
                0.284
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Optimize communication with Auditors"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.3,
                0.885,
                0.348
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "At the end of the consolidation process, Auditors receive the consolidated accounts on a support agreed beforehand (paper, Excel, pdf reports, readily access to the consolidation software)."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.363,
                0.885,
                0.445
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "After having received a \"Reporting Version 1\", some Auditors communicate their first remarks and ask to receive a \"Reporting Version 2\" so they can visualize the impact of the requested changes. Of course, this second reporting is to be compared with the first one and not with the reference consolidation. And the situation may be repeated several times."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.46,
                0.88,
                0.508
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "We would recommend negotiating with Auditors to produce a 'temporary version\" for audit purpose on which they hand over all their remarks. They receive then a \"final version\"."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.524,
                0.88,
                0.557
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "If possible, ask also to get some guarantee that the same team will audit the next consolidations, otherwise you will have to repeat the story each time."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.119,
                0.573,
                0.511,
                0.589
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "This is also a way to avoid wasting time."
        },
